{"id":"ointment","term":"Ointment","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Various fragrant preparations, also compounds for medical purposes, are so called (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 30:25\">Ex. 30:25</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 133:2\">Ps. 133:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 1:6\">Isa. 1:6</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Amos 6:6\">Amos 6:6</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 12:3\">John 12:3</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 18:13\">Rev. 18:13</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Exodus 30:25","Psalms 133:2","Isaiah 1:6","Amos 6:6","John 12:3","Revelation 18:13"]}